鱵, Pinyin zhēn, Zhuyin ㄓㄣ. 〔鱵鱼〕The body is slender, sub-cylindrical, with large eyes, small mouth, and slender jaw like a needle, so it is also called "needle fish". The dorsal fin is born on the back of the body and the anal fin is equal. It is a small fish that lives in shallow sea estuaries, and some can enter freshwater life.

〔鱵鱼〕体细长，亚圆筒形，眼大，口小，下颌细长如针，故亦称“针鱼”，背鳍生于身体后部，臀鳍与之相等。是生活于浅海河口的小型鱼类，有的也能进入淡水生活。

鱵字的汉语字典释义

[①]［zhēn］
［《廣韻》職深切，平侵，章。］
鱼名。鱼纲鱵科。又名针鱼。体细长，近圆形。下颌延长如针，故名。背鳍位于体之后部，臀鳍与之相等。栖息于浅海河口，有的种亦可进入淡水。

Chinese dictionary definition of words
[①]［zhēn］
["Guangyun" deep-seated, flat invasion, chapter. ]
The name of the fish. Fish class locust family. Also known as needle fish. The body is slender and nearly round. The mandible stretches like a needle, hence the name. The dorsal fin is located at the back of the body, and the anal fin is equal to it. Inhabits shallow sea estuaries, and some species can also enter fresh water.
